This paper deals with the task of object parsing, specifically in the context of human parsing. The paper proposes a novel approach for instance-level segmentation of human parts, which involves assigning each pixel in the image a part label as well as the identity of the object it belongs to. This task falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category, which is the most likely category for this paper. Additionally, the paper proposes a neural network architecture that is trained end-to-end, which involves the use of a differentiable Conditional Random Field (CRF) for reasoning about the identity of each part. This aspect of the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper involves the use of image processing techniques, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of natural language processing techniques, specifically in the context of parsing, which falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
